        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 11 at 6:18PM EDT by NWS Newport/Morehead City NC</headline>
        <description>At 618 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Blounts Creek, or 12 miles south of River Road, moving east at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Maribel, Askins, Aurora Ferry Terminal, Florence, Blounts Creek,
Pamlico Beach, Vandemere, Edward, Bayview Ferry Terminal, Royal,
Aurora, Cox Crossroads, Bonnerton, Mesic, Ernul, Core Point, Lowland,
Cayton, and South Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
